### 灰1 | _(1)F(u/)i_ [[fui1]]

$$
R
  ⽕ + 2
U
  U+7070
H
  May appear as either ⿸𠂇火 (assumed here) or ⿸厂火,
  depending on the font.
F
  ==
  - (F2.80 灰) 火灰石灰
  ==
W
  ====
  - [[Page~62 (1)灰]]
    ==
    - Ashes [[Kangxi: 死火餘㶳也, 火之滅者爲灰]], ashy;
    - lime;
    - dust;
    - to plaster;
    - _(2)fo (1)f(u/)i_
        [[fo2 fui1 火灰]],
        wood-ashes;
    - _t(')(a/)n(3) (1)f(u/)i_
        [[taan3 fui1 炭灰]],
        coal-ash;
    - _shek(9) (1)f(u/)i_
        [[sek6 fui1 石灰]],
        stone lime;
    - _(1)pan (4)long (1)f(u/)i_
        [[ban1 long4 fui1 檳榔灰]],
        betel lime;
    - _(1)f(u/)i (2)tsun_
        [[fui1 zeon2 灰燼]],
        embers;
    - _(4)ng(a/) (1)f(u/)i_
        [[ngaa4 fui1 牙灰]],
        tooth-powder;
    - _(1)f(u/)i (4)ts(')(e/)ung_
        [[fui1 coeng4 灰牆]],
        to plaster a wall.
    ==
  ====
C
  ==
  - Williams prints the headword as ⿸厂火,
    which is compatibility ideograph U+2F835.
  ==
P
  ++
  1. Charcoal.
  1. Grey.
  1. Disheartened.
  ++
L
  ====
  * 【灰】 (xwoj)
    ==
    - (_noun-like_) ash
    - (_noun-like_) charcoal
    ==
  ====
$$

### 魁1 | _(1)F(u/)i_ [[fui1]]

$$
R
  ⿁ + 4
  ⽃ + 10
U
  U+9B41
F
  ==
  - (F2.80 魁) 凡爲首者皆曰魁
  ==
W
  ====
  - [[Page~62 (1)魁]]
    ==
    - A star [[Kangxi: 星名]];
    - the head, chief [[Kangxi: 魁帥也, 魁猶首也]];
    - the highest or first of a class;
    - ~~monstrous~~ ``great`` [[Kangxi: 大也]];
    - _(4)(u:)n (1)f(u/)i_
        [[jyun4 fui1 元魁]],
        the chief;
    - _(1)f(u/)i (2)shau_
        [[fui1 sau2 魁首]],
        the first _k(u:)jin_ [[舉人]] graduate;
    - _(a/)(3) (1)f(u/)i_
        [[aa3 fui1 亞魁]],
        the second;
    - _(1)f(u/)i (1)sing_
        [[fui1 sing1 魁星]],
        the north star, the attendant of the god of Literature;
    - _(4)man (1)f(u/)i_
        [[man4 fui1 文魁]],
        the sign over the door of a _k(u:)jin_ [[舉人]] graduate.
    ==
  ====
C
  ==
  - Williams' "A star": Specifically, the first (or first four) of the Big Dipper (Kangxi: 魁北斗第一星也, 春秋緯曰瑤光第一至第四爲魁).
  ==
P
  ++
  1. A (small) mound (Kangxi: 小阜).
  1. A large ladle or dipper.
  1. A type of mollusc (Kangxi: 蜃蛤也).
  ++
L
  ====
  * 【魁】 (khwoj)
    ==
    - (_noun-like_) dipper, dipper-[mollusc]
    - (_noun-like_) mound
    - (_adjective-like_) chief
    - (_adjective-like_) great
    ==
  ====
$$
